SUMMARY:Fathering in the Age of the Apocalypse
LOCATION:London
DESCRIPTION:One show. Two dads. Thirteen years of questionable life choices
 . In 2013\, Tom and Haydn made a pact: they would have children as long-for
 m character research for a 60-minute comedy show about the collapse of civi
 lisation. Now\, thirteen years of sleep deprivation and school runs later\,
  they’ve arrived at the Camden Fringe to collect their 10% box office spl
 it. Tom wants a sophisticated\, barbed autopsy of the geopolitical landscap
 e—think The Rest is Politics with more panic. Haydn wants to shield himse
 lf from the end of days mainly with wigs\, maybe some hats. What follows is
  a high-stakes clash between intentionality and anarchy. A show for anyone 
 who fears for their children’s future\, even if they were sired for comed
 y purposes\, or anyone who suspects the apocalypse might just be one long S
 unday afternoon with nothing to watch on Netflix. Come for the promise of l
 ight entertainment. Stay for the safety of being underground.\nMore info: h
